race.comment: HEADBANGER (8) was well beaten first up at Pakenham when in the market, racing keenly off a long break having run well for second at Hawkesbury on debut when with the Waterhouse & Bott yard. She gets a tongue tie on here for the sharp Begg yard and with that run under the belt she's worth another chance. PACIFIC CHILL (9) resumes. She struggled badly on debut when striking a heavy track at Bendigo and was tipped out. She's won a jumpout leading into this campaign and it's likely worth ignoring her effort on debut. Look for improvement this time around. SAN MARCO KID (3) was outclassed in a G3 on debut before a long spell. He can be an improver this time around. GWEN'S GIRL (7) is lightly raced and has good speed. She'll be fitter off a solid fresh run and can give a sight.
